# WHAT IT IS
#   Cloudy Pad is "a free, open-source alternative to GeForce Now,
#   Blacknut, and similar cloud-gaming platforms".  It provisions a
#   GPU-equipped cloud instance on AWS / Azure / GCP / Paperspace /
#   Scaleway (or pairs an existing SSH-reachable machine), installs
#   NVIDIA drivers, Steam, Lutris, and the Sunshine streaming host,
#   then pairs your local Moonlight client to stream games over the
#   network.  Lifecycle management goes through Pulumi (provision)
#   and Ansible (configure), with first-class start/stop hooks to
#   keep cloud spend low between sessions.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from src/cli/program.ts —
#                       Commander v13 with `@commander-js/extra-
#                       typings`)
#   cloudypad [GLOBAL OPTIONS] <SUBCOMMAND> [args...]
#
#   Global options:
#     -v, --verbose <LEVEL>          Verbosity (0:silly..6:fatal;
#                                    alt env: CLOUDYPAD_LOG_LEVEL)
#     --version                      Show version
#     -h, --help                     Show help
#
#   Subcommands:
#     create <PROVIDER>              Create a new instance
#                                    Providers: aws | azure | gcp |
#                                               paperspace |
#                                               scaleway | ssh
#     update <PROVIDER>              Update an existing instance
#                                    (same provider set as create)
#
#     list                           List all instances
#       --format <FORMAT>              Output format (plain|json)
#                                      [default: plain]
#
#     start <NAME>                   Start an instance
#       --wait                         Wait for instance to be
#                                      fully started
#       --timeout <SECS>               Wait timeout (only with
#                                      --wait)
#       --retries <N>                  Retry count
#       --retry-delay <SECS>           Retry delay
#       --force-pulumi-cancel          Force-cancel a Pulumi update
#                                      in flight
#       --ansible-args-override <ARGS> Pass-through args to Ansible
#                                      (override default)
#
#     stop <NAME>                    Stop an instance
#       --wait / --timeout <SECS> / --retries / --retry-delay /
#       --force-pulumi-cancel
#
#     restart <NAME>                 Restart an instance
#       --wait / --timeout <SECS> / --retries / --retry-delay /
#       --force-pulumi-cancel
#
#     get <NAME>                     Get state + status (running,
#                                    provisioned, configured,
#                                    ready)
#
#     provision <NAME>               Deploy or update Cloud
#                                    resources via Pulumi
#       --yes                          Auto-approve
#       --retries / --retry-delay / --force-pulumi-cancel
#
#     configure <NAME>               Connect via SSH and install
#                                    drivers / packages via
#                                    Ansible
#       --retries / --retry-delay / --force-pulumi-cancel /
#       --ansible-args-override
#
#     deploy <NAME>                  Combined provision + configure
#       (same options as configure + provision)
#
#     destroy <NAME>                 Destroy the cloud instance
#       --yes / --retries / --retry-delay / --force-pulumi-cancel
#
#     pair <NAME>                    Pair Moonlight client to the
#                                    Sunshine host running on the
#                                    instance
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   Direct dependency on `@aws-sdk/client-ec2 ^3.614.0`,
#   `@aws-sdk/client-s3 ^3.614.0`, `@aws-sdk/client-account
#   ^3.616.0`, `@aws-sdk/client-service-quotas ^3.726.0`,
#   `@aws-sdk/client-sts ^3.730.0`, `@aws-sdk/credential-providers
#   ^3.616.0`, and `@aws-sdk/s3-request-presigner ^3.614.0`
#   declared in package.json — the modular `@aws-sdk/client-*`
#   v3 family is THE canonical Node.js AWS SDK maintained by AWS
#   (aws/aws-sdk-js-v3, 3.4K+ stars; ~150 per-service npm packages
#   under the `@aws-sdk/*` scope).  aws-sdk-js-v3 is the Smithy-
#   codegen modular rewrite of the legacy aws-sdk-js v2:  every
#   service ships as its own npm package, every API operation is
#   a typed `Command` class invoked via `client.send(new Command
#   (...))`, every paginator is a `paginateXxx(...)` generator,
#   and the `@aws-sdk/credential-providers` package wraps the
#   complete credential chain (env, shared file, INI profile,
#   IMDSv2, SSO, IAM Identity Center, ECS / Fargate task role,
#   web identity, processes, AssumeRole, AssumeRoleWithSAML,
#   AssumeRoleWithWebIdentity).  cloudypad's
#   `src/providers/aws/sdk-client.ts` builds an `EC2Client`,
#   `S3Client`, `AccountClient`, `STSClient`, and
#   `ServiceQuotasClient` from `fromIni` / `fromNodeProviderChain`
#   credentials, and the `@aws-sdk/s3-request-presigner` is used
#   for the Sunshine-config presign-upload path.  Verified via:
#     gh api repos/PierreBeucher/cloudypad/contents/package.json
#       → "@aws-sdk/client-ec2": "^3.614.0"
#       → "@aws-sdk/client-s3": "^3.614.0"
#       → "@aws-sdk/client-account": "^3.616.0"
#       → "@aws-sdk/client-service-quotas": "^3.726.0"
#       → "@aws-sdk/client-sts": "^3.730.0"
#       → "@aws-sdk/credential-providers": "^3.616.0"
#       → "@aws-sdk/s3-request-presigner": "^3.614.0"
#       → "bin": {"cloudypad": "./src/cli/main.js"}
#     gh api repos/PierreBeucher/cloudypad/contents/src/cli/
#         program.ts
#       → program.command('create'|'update'|'list'|'start
#           <name>'|'stop <name>'|'restart <name>'|'get
#           <name>'|'provision <name>'|'configure <name>'|
#           'deploy <name>'|'destroy <name>'|'pair <name>')
#   This entry is the TS-Node=144 leader bump that CLOSES Axis
#   89 (AWS SDK / aws-sdk-rust) at 1/1/1 three-language symmetry
#   — pairing Rust=aws-sdk-iam via awslabs/iam-policy-autopilot
#   (R945 _iam-policy-autopilot), Go=aws-sdk-go-v2 via
#   cossacklabs/acra (R946 _acra-server), and TS-Node=
